label.value: posteroventral corner of the first valvifer

value.value: The corner of the first valvifer that is adjacent to the intervalvifer articulation.

label.value: length of anterior area of second valvifer

value.value: The anatomical line that is parallel with the longitudinal body axis and the shortest among the anatomical lines that extend between the anterior and posterior margins of the anterior area of the second valvifer.
The anatomical line that is parallel with the longitudinal body axis and the shortest among the anatomical lines that extend between the anterior and posterior margins of female T9.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the mandibular teeth.
The row of setae that is located on the medial wall of the galeo-lacinial complex proximal to the coeloconic sensilla of galea.
The campaniform sensillum that is on the ventral premental face.
The concavity on the distal margin of the prementum delimiting medially the site of attachment of the labial palp.
The sclerite that is part of the labial palp.
The styloconic sensillum that is located apically on the glossa.
The apophysis that is located proximomedially on the female S7.
The conjunctiva that connects the female T8 with female T9 and is tubular.
The sulcus that corresponds to the ridge that is continuous with the third phragma and extends between the metapleural apodeme.
The tooth tooth that is located on the posterior surface of the lower tooth.

The anatomical line that is the longest vertical diameter of the compound eye in frontal view.

The scrobe that is on the mesopectus and accommodates the profemur.

The setal patch that is elongate, is adjacent and extends just lateral to the plica and is composed of posteriorly directed and apressed setae that inserts into the retinaculum when the fore wing is in a flexed position.

label.value: anterodistal notch of the fore wing

value.value: The notch that is on the anterior wing margin, is adacent to the anterior end of the poststigmal fold line.

label.value: posterodistal notch of the fore wing

value.value: The notch on the posterior wing margin that is adjacent to the posterior end of the discal fold.
The median anatomical line that extends between the transverse carina on petiole and the posterior margin of the petiole.
The anatomical line that is the shortest between the anterior tentorial pits.
The projection that is located anterolaterally on the epicnemial carina.
The scrobe that is located ventrally of the propodeal foramen and accommodates the proximal area of the petiole.

The anatomical line that is the longest horizontal diameter of the cranium in frontal view.

The median anatomical line that extends between the anterior margin of the ventral region of the metapectus and the distal end of the projection bearing the medial coxal condyle of the metapectus.
The anatomical line that extends between the proximal and distal margins of an anatomical structure.
The median anatomical line that is the longest between the anterior margin of the head and the propodeal foramen in dorsal view.

The carina on the posterodorsal mesoscutellum that is dorsally convex.

The area that is median and separates the scutellar foveae.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the distal notch on the second valvula and the associated dentition and flexible flap.

The area of the pronotal plate that is posterior to the pronotal foveae.
